Cook, you are right.  The American left, Bill Clinton, Sen. Chris Dodd, Jane Fonda, Tom Hayden and others were involved in delivering South Vietnam to the communists.  Of course, all those Hollywood, New York and Washington leftists who celebrated in 1975 now hope that Americans will forget that they have the dubious distinction of having participated in the killing of 58,000 Americans.<br>
I don't believe in reformed ex-'60s radicals, some of whon are now on the conservative chicken circuit, ratting out their old comrades and doing mea culpas.<br>
The reason I don't trust them is this:  If they were stupid enough to hate America and to think communism offered something better, and if they were immoral enough to vilify their fellow Americans in uniform and vicious enough to betray them while they were fighting and dying, then they are most likely still stupid, immoral and vicious.<br>
Never trust converts.  They may have left one side, but they bring the same baggage to the new side, and who wants to be allied with stupid, immoral and vicious people?  A bad dog is a bad dog  no matter whose yard he occupies.<br>
Of course, most of the '60s radicals haven't even pretended to reform and are now ensconced in various capitalist positions, as tenured professors and in the government.<br>
They were full of shit then and they still are now.<br>
I've noticed that despite TV's love of documentaries, I haven't seen one showing Mrs. Ted Turner sitting at a North Vietnamese anti-aircraft gun, grinning like an idiot.<br>
